HB 172 Original 2026 Regular Session Newell
Abstract: Provides for state supplemental pay to fire protection officers employed by an
airport authority
Present constitution authorizes the legislature to provide state supplemental pay by law to
sworn, commissioned law enforcement officers employed by the state or its political
subdivisions and for fire protection officers employed by a port authority.
Proposed constitution retains present constitution and authorizes the legislature to provide
state supplemental pay by law to fire protection officers employed by an airport authority.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held Nov. 3, 2026.
(Amends Const. Art. X, §10(A)(1)(b))
